    {
      "type": "context",
      "agent": "user",
      "content": "# CURRENT STEP SCOPE\n\n**Step 1 of 5**: Randomize headless mode and viewport size\n\n## Goal\n## Goal\nModify `src/main.ts` to enhance stealth by randomizing the browser viewport dimensions and enabling Camoufox's virtual headless mode. This reduces fingerprinting consistency across requests.\n\n## Task Type\nCode modification in `src/main.ts` – update the `camoufoxLaunchOptions()` call and add a viewport randomization utility.\n\n## Technical Context from Codebase\n- File: `src/main.ts` lines 44-57 contain `PlaywrightCrawler` creation. Specifically, lines 50-55:\n  ```ts\n  const launchOptions = await camoufoxLaunchOptions({\n      headless: true,\n      proxy: await proxyConfiguration?.newUrl(),\n      geoip: true,\n  });\n  ```\n- `camoufoxLaunchOptions` expects `LaunchOptions` from `camoufox-js` (v0.9.3), which supports:\n  - `window: [number, number]` – fixed window size\n  - `headless: boolean | \"virtual\"` – `\"virtual\"` enables a virtual display (Xvfb) for complete headless masking\n- No viewport randomization currently exists; viewport is browser default.\n- Camoufox's built-in stealth already spoofs many fingerprints, but a fixed viewport is less realistic.\n- The Docker base image `apify/actor-node-playwright-camoufox:24-1.60.0` includes Xvfb, so `headless: \"virtual\"` will work.\n\n## Action\n1. Create a constant array of common desktop viewport sizes (width × height) in `src/main.ts` before the crawler creation.\n2. Add a function `getRandomViewport()` that picks a random pair from the array.\n3. Modify the `camoufoxLaunchOptions()` call to:\n   - Set `window` to the randomly chosen dimensions.\n   - Change `headless` from `true` to `\"virtual\"`.\n4. Ensure the viewport is randomized once per crawl run (not per page) by calling `getRandomViewport()` before the crawler constructor.\n5. If `headless: \"virtual\"` causes issues in certain environments (e.g., CI without Xvfb), fall back to `headless: true` with a log warning.\n\n## Reasoning\n- Randomizing viewport mimics real user diversity, making automation harder to detect.\n- `headless: \"virtual\"` uses a virtual display, so the browser thinks it has a real screen (no `navigator.webdriver` flags). Camoufox already hides headless, but virtual mode adds another layer.\n- Using Camoufox's built-in `window` option, not Playwright's `setViewportSize`, because Camoufox must apply its fingerprint adjustments at launch.\n- Keeping the random pick at crawler start (not per page) avoids recomputing launch options mid-session, which is unsupported.\n\n## Implementation Details\n- In `src/main.ts`, after imports and before `Actor.init()`, add:\n  ```ts\n  const COMMON_VIEWPORTS: [number, number][] = [\n      [1920, 1080],\n      [1366, 768],\n      [1440, 900],\n      [1536, 864],\n      [1280, 720],\n  ];\n\n  function getRandomViewport(): [number, number] {\n      return COMMON_VIEWPORTS[Math.floor(Math.random() * COMMON_VIEWPORTS.length)];\n  }\n  ```\n- Replace lines 50-55 with:\n  ```ts\n  const viewport = getRandomViewport();\n  const headlessMode = process.env.HEADLESS_VIRTUAL !== 'false' ? 'virtual' as const : true;\n  const launchOptions = await camoufoxLaunchOptions({\n      headless: headlessMode,\n      window: viewport,\n      proxy: await proxyConfiguration?.newUrl(),\n      geoip: true,\n  });\n  log.info(`Using viewport ${viewport[0]}×${viewport[1]} and headless mode: ${headlessMode}`);\n  ```\n- The environment variable `HEADLESS_VIRTUAL` (set to `'false'`) allows overriding for CI or environments without Xvfb.\n- No changes to `useIncognitoPages` or other options.\n\n## Error Handling and Edge Cases\n- If `headless: \"virtual\"` is used and Xvfb is missing, Camoufox will throw at launch. The catch block around crawler creation (if any) should handle it. If not present, we add a try-catch around `crawler.run()` with a fallback to `headless: true` after logging the error.\n- Viewport randomization must be deterministic per run; using `Math.random()` is fine because each run gets a fresh seed.\n- If proxy is not available (null), we still proceed without proxy – viewport randomization still applies.\n\n## Validation\n- Run `npm run start:dev` (or `apify run`) locally. The log should show the chosen viewport and headless mode.\n- Crawl https://apify.com and verify that pages load correctly, no errors due to viewport/headless change.\n- Run `npm test` to ensure existing integration test (which crawls apify.com) still passes.\n- Optionally inspect browser fingerprints via a detection site (e.g., fingerprintjs.com) to confirm viewport is non-default.\n\n## Dependencies and Inputs\n- No new npm packages.\n- Input schema unchanged – stealth is internal.\n- The environment variable `HEADLESS_VIRTUAL` can be set in `.actor/actor.json` under `environmentVariables` for CI, but not required.\n\n## Constraints\n- Viewport must be set via `window` in launchOptions, not via Playwright's `page.setViewportSize()` after launch – Camoufox's fingerprinting depends on it.\n- Randomization occurs once at crawler start; per-crawl-run randomness is sufficient.\n- Must maintain compatibility with the existing proxy and geoip setup.\n\n## API and Integration Impact\n- No impact on dataset output or router.\n- Crawler behavior unchanged – still uses same `preNavigationHooks` (not modified in this step).\n\n## Performance and Scalability Notes\n- Viewport randomization adds negligible overhead.\n- `headless: \"virtual\"` may use slightly more memory due to virtual display, but acceptable for typical runs.\n\n## Documentation Impact\n- Add a comment in `src/main.ts` explaining the viewport randomization and virtual headless mode.\n- Optionally update `README.md` if present, but not required.\n\nThis is the ONLY task you must complete in this iteration. Do not work on other steps.",
